To show a custom name instead of the client ID when creating and editing files in SharePoint, you can use the `EnsureUser` method with the `LoginName` property to specify the user's login name. However, this might not be feasible if you don't have the user's login name.

A better approach would be to get the user's details from the `context.Web.EnsureUser` method and then set the `Name` property to the custom name you want to display.

Here's an example:

```csharp
